dence interval, 1.2-12.5) (P=.02). CONCLUSIONS: Our findings indicate an association between a common genetic variation in ADRB1 and myocardial ischemic response to mental stress in patients with coronary artery disease. This polymorphic genetic marker may help identify patients at increased risk for mental stress-induced adverse outcomes.},
