 history, heart failure, depression, posttraumatic stress disorder, and heart rate/blood pressure reactivity.$\backslash$r$\backslash$n$\backslash$r$\backslash$nConclusions: Autonomic factors, most notably reduced LF HRV reactivity, predict MSI in CAD patients. This implies reduced BRS and autonomic inflexibility as an important pathophysiological component of the ischemic response to mental stress.},
